## Build Paths

Since you found Outlearn, chances are you are "that dev" on your team who finds all sorts of great resources.  You know that every popular technology you need to learn already has dozens of blog posts and tutorials around the web explaining how it works.  If only you could get everyone at your company to read and understand them!

Here's the trick: _someone_ has to pick them out, settle on the order, and provide some local context, i.e. "why is this useful to us?"  **Outlearn makes all that easy as cake.** (`assert(!cake.is_a?(Lie))`)

<!-- @task, "hasDeliverable" : true, "text" : "What's one topic you wish you could snap your fingers and teach your dev team?" -->

We want to make you the hero that organizes all that useful material.  

